def pivot_table(
    data,
    values=None,
    index=None,
    columns=None,
    aggfunc="mean",
    fill_value=None,
    margins=False,
    dropna=True,
    margins_name="All",
    observed=False
) -> DataFrame:
    keys = index + columns

    if isinstance(aggfunc, list):
        agg_results = []
        for func in aggfunc:
            grouped = data.groupby(keys, observed=observed)
            agged = grouped.agg(func)
            if dropna and not agged.empty:
                agged = agged.dropna(how="all")

            agg_results.append(agged)

        table = concat(agg_results, axis=1, keys=[getattr(func, "__name__", func) for func in aggfunc])
    else:
        grouped = data.groupby(keys, observed=observed)
        agged = grouped.agg(aggfunc)
        if dropna and not agged.empty:
            agged = agged.dropna(how="all")
        table = agged

    # additional processing code remains the same as the original function

    return table
